Using correlated traits from predicted individuals, the training population size can be reduced up to 30% of its size without significantly affecting the predictive ability of the model (Fig. 5). In addition, the inclusion of marker information improved 2–14% the predictive ability of multi-trait models for W and there was no improvement for L trait (Fig. 5).Fig. 5
